---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Worship — Praying Inside the Story"
  description="A six-step Ignatian Contemplation framework for entering a Gospel scene with your imagination — stepping into Scripture as a participant, not just a reader."
>
  <a class="overlay-back" href="/worship/takeaways/">&#8592; Back to Takeaways</a>
  <a class="overlay-close" href="/" aria-label="Close">&times;</a>

  <div class="takeaways-content pp-page">
    <span class="takeaways-tag">Worship</span>
    <h1 class="takeaways-title">Praying Inside the Story</h1>
    <p class="pp-subtitle">Six steps for entering a Gospel scene — and letting it speak to you.</p>

    <!-- Quick-jump nav -->
    <div class="pp-nav">
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-settle">1. Settle</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-choose">2. Choose a Scene</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-enter">3. Enter the Story</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-stay">4. Stay &amp; Notice</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-speak">5. Speak with Jesus</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-receive">6. Receive &amp; Record</a>
    </div>

    <div class="pp-steps">

      <section class="pp-step" id="step-settle">
        <h2 class="pp-step-heading"><span class="pp-step-num">Step 1</span> Settle</h2>
        <p class="pp-step-text">Before you open Scripture, open yourself. Find a quiet place and sit comfortably. Take three slow, deliberate breaths and let the noise of your day fall away — the to-do list, the unfinished conversations, the phone still buzzing in your pocket. Silently invite the Holy Spirit to lead your imagination. This is not a mental exercise; it is a prayer. You are not trying to conjure a feeling — you are asking God to use your mind as a means of meeting with Him. Before you do anything else, notice what you are carrying into this moment, and notice whether you are actually willing to set it down. Stay here for two or three minutes before moving on.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="pp-step" id="step-choose">
        <h2 class="pp-step-heading"><span class="pp-step-num">Step 2</span> Choose a Scene</h2>
        <p class="pp-step-text">Select one Gospel passage — a scene with movement, tension, or a direct encounter with Jesus. Read it through slowly, twice. Don't analyze it yet; just let the story settle in your mind. Take Blind Bartimaeus (Mark 10:46–52) as an example: a man shouting from the side of a dusty road outside Jericho, the crowd trying to silence him, and Jesus stopping to ask what sounds like an obvious question — <em>What do you want me to do for you?</em> Notice whether a character in the scene already pulls at you before you have even closed your eyes. Shorter, more vivid scenes work better than long discourses — you want action, people, and place.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="pp-step" id="step-enter">
        <h2 class="pp-step-heading"><span class="pp-step-num">Step 3</span> Enter the Story</h2>
        <p class="pp-step-text">Close your eyes and step inside the scene. Ignatius called this the "composition of place" — building the setting in your mind with as much sensory detail as possible. With Bartimaeus, you are on the road outside Jericho: afternoon heat, the smell of dust and sweat, the noise of a large crowd pressing forward. What does the ground feel like underfoot? Where are you standing — in the middle of the crowd, at its edge, or are you Bartimaeus himself, cloak thrown aside, scrambling to your feet? Your position in the scene is not a trivial detail; it tells you something about where you are with God right now. Choose where you feel drawn, and let the scene begin to move.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="pp-step" id="step-stay">
        <h2 class="pp-step-heading"><span class="pp-step-num">Step 4</span> Stay &amp; Notice</h2>
        <p class="pp-step-text">Let the scene unfold without forcing it. Don't rush toward the spiritual lesson — stay inside the experience. When Jesus stops and calls for Bartimaeus, watch what happens in your body. When the crowd suddenly reverses — <em>Take heart; rise, he is calling you</em> — notice whether that shift registers somewhere in you. When Jesus asks <em>What do you want me to do for you?</em>, pay attention if that question lands somewhere unexpected. These are moments of consolation and desolation — warmth, peace, or longing on one side; resistance, numbness, or the urge to stop on the other. Both are data. The moments that surprise you or unsettle you are often the most important ones. Sit here for at least five minutes. Longer is better.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="pp-step" id="step-speak">
        <h2 class="pp-step-heading"><span class="pp-step-num">Step 5</span> Speak with Jesus</h2>
        <p class="pp-step-text">Ignatius called this the "colloquy" — a heart-to-heart conversation. Still inside the scene, turn toward Jesus and speak honestly. Not formally. Not piously. The way you would talk to someone who already knows everything about you and loves you anyway. Tell him what you felt watching Bartimaeus receive his sight, or what it stirred up to be in the crowd, or what it cost to imagine yourself as the one shouting. Ask him what he wants you to understand. Then be quiet and listen. You may sense a response — a word, an image, a feeling of peace or conviction. Receive whatever comes without forcing it. The goal is not to hear an audible voice; it is to be genuinely present with the one you are talking to.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="pp-step" id="step-receive">
        <h2 class="pp-step-heading"><span class="pp-step-num">Step 6</span> Receive &amp; Record</h2>
        <p class="pp-step-text">Slowly come back out of the scene. Before anything else, pick up a pen and write down one word, one image, or one sentence that stayed with you — not a summary, just what lingered. Maybe it was the thrown cloak. Maybe it was the crowd reversing. Maybe it was the question itself. This small act of writing is how you bring the encounter back into your daily life, and how you begin to notice patterns across multiple sessions. Over time your journal becomes a record of what God is saying to you through Scripture — not what the commentaries say, but what he said to you specifically, in those scenes, on those days. Carry the image or word into your day. Return to it before you sleep.</p>
      </section>

    </div><!-- /.pp-steps -->

    <!-- Suggested Scenes -->
    <div class="pp-scenes-section">
      <span class="pp-scenes-label">Suggested Scenes to Try</span>
      <div class="pp-scenes-grid">
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Mark 4:35–41</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">The Storm on the Sea</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">John 8:1–11</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">The Woman Caught in Adultery</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Mark 10:46–52</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Blind Bartimaeus</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Luke 10:38–42</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Mary &amp; Martha</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Matthew 14:22–33</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Walking on Water</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">John 20:11–18</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Mary at the Tomb</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Luke 15:11–32</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">The Prodigal Son</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">John 21:1–19</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Breakfast on the Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AI Prompt -->
    <div class="pp-ai-prompt">
      <span class="pp-ai-label">AI Prompt</span>
      <p>I want to practice Ignatian Contemplation. Walk me through each of the six steps one at a time, pausing after each to ask me the reflection questions. Don't move on until I've answered honestly — push back gently if my responses feel surface-level. Help me stay inside the scene rather than jumping to analysis. At the end, help me write a short journal entry capturing what I noticed and what I want to carry into my week.</p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /.takeaways-content -->
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  /* ─── Page header ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-subtitle {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #7a7368;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─── Quick-jump nav ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.2);
  }

  .pp-nav-link {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #7a7368;
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.5);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .pp-nav-link:hover {
    background: #6a6156;
    color: #f3efe9;
    border-color: #6a6156;
  }

  /* ─── Steps prose ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .pp-step {
    border-left: 2px solid rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.35);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pp-step-heading {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #3d3830;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .pp-step-num {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b79c5c;
  }

  .pp-step-text {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #5e554b;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .pp-step-text em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #3d3830;
  }

  /* ─── Suggested Scenes ──────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-scenes-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .pp-scenes-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b79c5c;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pp-scenes-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pp-scene-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.35);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .pp-scene-ref {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #8a7e6e;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pp-scene-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #3d3830;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* ─── AI Prompt ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-ai-prompt {
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .pp-ai-label {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #f3efe9;
    background: #6a6156;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.65rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .pp-ai-prompt p {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    color: #5e554b;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ─── Responsive ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .pp-scenes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .pp-step {
      padding-left: 1rem;
    }

    .pp-scenes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .pp-ai-prompt {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
